Q1 = df['Price'].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df['Price'].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1

lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

df = df[(df['Price'] >= lower_bound) & (df['Price'] <= upper_bound)]

ax.set_xlabel('Average Prices', fontsize=12)
ax.set_ylabel('Places', fontsize=12)

# Show the plot
plt.show()

# Count the availability status per place
availability_counts = df.groupby('Place')['Availability'].value_counts().unstack(fill_value=0)

# Calculate the percentage of availability per place
availability_percentage = (availability_counts['Yes'] / (availability_counts['Yes'] + availability_counts['No'])) * 100

# Convert to DataFrame for better readability
availability_percentage_df = availability_percentage.reset_index(name='Availability %')
availability_percentage_df

from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder

label_encoder = LabelEncoder()

# List of categorical columns to encode
categorical_columns = ['Place', 'Hood', 'Type', 'Availability']  # Add any other categorical columns if necessary

for column in categorical_columns:
    df[column] = label_encoder.fit_transform(df[column])

# Display the first few rows of the dataframe after encoding
print(df.head())

# Select numerical columns to compute the correlation
numeric_data = df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number])

# Calculate the correlation matrix
correlation_matrix = numeric_data.corr()

# Display the correlation matrix
print(correlation_matrix)

# Generate a heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, fmt=".2f", cmap='coolwarm', square=True, cbar_kws={"shrink": .8})
plt.title('Correlation Heatmap')
plt.show()

from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score, silhouette_samples

silhouette_coefficients = []
# Notice you start at 2 clusters for silhouette coefficient
for k in range(2, 10):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, init= "k-means++",n_init= 12,max_iter= 300)
    kmeans.fit(X)
    score = silhouette_score(X, kmeans.labels_)
    silhouette_coefficients.append(score)

silhouette_coefficients
